So I have seen their Instagram and couldnt wait to try their food. I went there last Saturday for breakfast, the girl at the register was very nice and informative.  My husband and I had their breakfast sandwiches, I had mine with the sausage which was very delicious, the size of the sandwich was decent as well, we also ordered a side of potatoes which were very tasty (wish they gave you more) . My only issue is the wait time.  We waited over 40 min for our food and our kids were OVER it by time we got our food. I will be back in Hope's that maybe they were having an off day. I hope the wait time is better next time.
Good lemon pepper wings.

I was so exited to come back to Tampa to try this place after hearing about it on the Judy Tour. Instagram photos of the food looked amazing. I made it back and I am very disappointed. Portions are very small,  wait time is over 40 minutes, food is not seasoned enough, and my order was incorrect. After our food was ready we realized there was no utensils in our to go bag and it took another 5 to 10 minutes just to get utensils. I ordered a chicken and shrimp pasta and when I got back to the hotel I realized the pasta only had chicken. We also ordered the seafood fries and the portion was very small to begin with and very little seafood. The pasta and fries came out to a little over $30 with tax. Definitely not worth it and will not be returning.

The food is delicious and well seasoned! However, the time that it takes to get your food is extremely long. This was my second visit and each wait time was at least 45 mins. My initial visit took longer due to it being ONE cook on duty. I understand the hard work and time it takes to serve fresh food but some things can be tweaked. The seafood fries taste just as amazing as how the pictures look on Instagram! So if you have the TIME do stop by and try them. 😊

I have been twice on the weekend, and this place  is very small & not ran well. I have yet to try the food yet because they were either out of what I want or  place was full due to it having about 5 tables for you sit
They have the most incredible food,I love they food to death,today was the day I had to try the fries with crab meat n lobster n I must say it was bussing lol

Wings where undercooked. As much as I wanted to come back. Didn’t like the wait. showed up about 2hrs after being opened during the week. Only one person in front, still waited over 40min for wings. ( and they where undercooked) I don’t understand.unless they weren’t prepared. only thing I could think of is the chef on duty threw the wings without being thawed into the fryer. 🤦🏽‍♂️ Would hate to get into this tiny place on a busy evening.

Good food (would give it 5 stars) but poor customer service! Had to ask for eating Utensils after hostess/server said that she would bring it to me 15 minutes later. Also, she didn’t bring me the red velvet cake and I had to ask! Furthermore, I didn’t even receive the dessert I asked for to-go, it was half eaten corn on the cob!!!!! I wish I would have double checked it before leaving. Ugh, I was so mad I would have turned my car around but I had a flight to catch. Please hire better help!!

I loved it me and my friend got there and it was so refreshing. From the people to the decor to the wall signing in the back. The vibe and music. I ordered wings and fries but these fries baby are bomb. The chicken salad fresh and the crazy doughnut brownie cookie shake. Come get cozy cause baby when i say these Queens are killing it. Be patient and courteous.

Please don’t take this as a negetive. I enjoyed the service, food, atmosphere and surroundings. As a native of Tampa I hung out on Main Street hitting all the clubs in the area. Bar b que king was spot back in the day, just like you are now. I remember when this spot was a pool hall. Enough down memory lane for me.What I didn’t enjoy was the loud explicit rap lyrics from the video channel. Everyone is not in to rap, but there is a better why it can be played without disturbing customers. I will return again so please don’t take this review as a negative. That’s the only reason I couldn’t rate you 5 stars.  Keep up the GREAT JOB !!!!

Wow so this place could use a little bit of organization and time management. My fourth time visiting and I've had to endure longer than usual waits, menu items that have ran out, cold food because of the long wait time and food portion inconsistent. My last visit I waited over 30 minutes which is a bit overkill. I understand they want to make a great reputation of "made to order" but this is a bit much. It was jam packed in a small space. I had my newborn and 3year old with me in which we waited in the car, they both took a 30 minute nap and woke up and food still not ready. Everytime I try to support it's either they are out of food, the truck didn't come that day, or they have shrimp but no salad (which was my favorite thing on the menu), sweet potato fries but no fire/ice, wings fried too hard, seafood fries yet the fries were cold and soggy, and lobster Mac n cheese with hardly any lobster. Not too mention overcooked Mac and under seasoned food. With all the hassle and price paid, I don't think I will be coming back. They never have 2 things that match.

Food was hot and the wait was long, but expected since everything seems to be cooked to order. The seating is minimal and outside ambiance is very local: to-go orders may be your best bet.

For the price of the food I would expect better, the location is ok but not enough seating inside. You have to pay and tip before getting your food. I don't see me taking the 40min drive again.
